article.headline: San Diego St. 86, Navy 76
article.story: EDS: San Diego St. 86, Navy 76. SAN DIEGO (AP) -- Lorrenzo Wade scored 18 points and Billy White added 17 to lift San Diego State to an 86-76 victory over Navy on Monday night. San Diego State (9-2) had trouble shaking the Midshipmen until a 3 1/2-minute stretch where the Aztecs went from being tied at 61 to taking a 74-61 lead with 4:32 left in the game. White scored five points in the 13-0 run, and Richie Williams and Kelvin Davis hit 3-pointers. Greg Sprink led Navy (3-8) with 26 points on 11-of-14 shooting from the field. The Aztecs extended their home winning streak to 11 games as they overcame the Midshipmen's 15-of-33 effort from 3-point range. Chris Harris, who finished with 22 points, had six 3-pointers and Sprink added four. Davis had 15 points and Kyle Spain added 14 points and nine rebounds for San Diego State.
